\ did-you-mean: the unknown-word error names the nearest dictionary word
\ (Levenshtein over codepoints; allowed distance 1 for 2-character tokens,
\ 2 for longer, none for 1-character tokens; internal words excluded;
\ in-scope locals included while compiling; nearest wins, newest on ties).

filtr                \ (did you mean filter?)
transposr            \ (did you mean transpose?)
swpa                 \ (did you mean swap?)
qzqzqz               \ (no word within distance 2 -> plain error)
q                    \ (1-character token -> plain error)
: f | total | 0 to total totl ;   \ (a local is suggested too)

\ distance ties break by use frequency (counted over the embedded library's
\ own compilation), then by longest common prefix; transposition costs 1
swop                 \ (did you mean swap? — not stop; swap is frequent)
ovr                  \ (did you mean over?)
dip                  \ (did you mean dup?)
swpa                 \ (did you mean swap? — transposition, distance 1)
ot                   \ (did you mean to? — 2-character transposition)
